    "Additionallyï¿½ there has been a focus on AI initiativesï¿½ instructional unitsï¿½ and tools (Marques et al., 2020ï¿½ Gresse Von Wangenheiï¿½ï¿½ and Hauckï¿½ 2020; Sanusi et al., 2023; Lim et al., 2023; Heintz and Roos, 2021; Heinemann et al.ï¿½ 2018) ï¿½ along with the evaluation of the effectiveness of such AI education interventions (Rizvi et al.ï¿½ 2023).",
    "While ï¿½uch of the recent work on ML in K-12 has focused ï¿½ostly on definitional issuesï¿½ toolsï¿½ and early interventions, much less attention has been focused on the underlying theories of learning and rigorous pedagogical foundations that inform the design and implementation of these instructional ideas and approaches.",
    "As noted by UNESCO (2022) ï¿½ there is also an evident need for involving various stakeholders in co-designing curriculum materials, tools, and scaffolding strategies for ensuring that the AI curriculums are pedagogically sound and actionable in practice.",
    "In response to these pressing needs, this paper introduces the theoretical foundations, design principles, and cross-boundary co-design process that engaged teachers and researchers to co-develop new educational practices, curriculum materials, and educational technology for facilitating the learning of ML in K-9 education in Finland.",
    "In Finland, as in many other countries, AI is a new topic in schools, as well as in teacher education."
